The paper deals with scheduling tasks on a single-processor system, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also proposes an allocator that minimizes the number of rescheduled tasks, which involves making decisions based on certain measures of the system's flexibility, indicating a possible application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also deals with the optimization of the allocator, which involves analyzing the system's behavior and performance, indicating a possible application of control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
